properties.Title: GNV, FL - Community Read - MLK's "Where Do We Go From Here"
properties.Description:
Join us in reading Dr. King's "Where Do We Go From Here: Chaos or Community?"

We will host a discussion about Dr. King's book, including it's role in Andrew Yang's vision for creating universal basic income, on MLK day at Cypress & Grove. All are welcome.

[From Wiki]
Where Do We Go from Here: Chaos or Community? is a 1967 book by African-American minister, Nobel Peace Prize laureate, and social justice campaigner Martin Luther King, Jr. Advocating for human rights and a sense of hope, it was King's fourth and last book before his assassination. He spent a long period in isolation, living in a rented residence in Jamaica with no telephone, composing the book.It later lapsed out of print until Beacon Press published an expanded edition in 2010, which featured a new introduction passage by King's long-time friend Vincent Gordon Harding and a foreword by King's wife, Coretta Scott King. The book received critical acclaim, its revamped version being highlighted as a 2011 University Press Book for Public and Secondary School Libraries and recommended for use in teaching.

- 6:00: Welcome & Group Introductions
- 6:30: Texting & Phone Bank Onboarding

- If you want to make calls it is helpful to bring a charged laptop/tablet or at minimum please bring a charged cell phone to make calls or send texts.
- There are several ways to mask your number for calling and via our texting app.
- Texting Instructions: http://bit.ly/35Qhi9Q Video: http://bit.ly/2pzrPpl

(it willl take about an hour to study up then you take a quiz before you get approved to send texts)

properties.Title: MIAMI, FL - CRITICAL MASS CROWD-YANGING
properties.Description:
From the Miami Bike Scene website:
“Critical Mass is a cycling event typically held on the last Friday of every month; its purpose is not usually formalized beyond the direct action of meeting at a set location and time and traveling as a group through city or town streets on bicycles.”

For November there were HUNDREDS of cyclists in attendance. These are all mostly local people, of all demographics. They all gather at the starting point on their bike at the start of the event, and just hang out until it begins. That’s where we’ll be operating. We’ll be handing out business cards and engaging in conversations if anyone is open to it.

The official time for gathering at the starting line is 6:30, the biking starts at 7:15. I wanted to get started at 6:15 to catch the early birds as well. That’s only about an hour to Yang hundreds of riders. The more of us there, and the earlier we start, the more people we can get to :)

I will be at the starting line (coordinates below) wearing a neon pink cap to provide everyone with cards to hand out. Should be hard to miss, but I’ll be checking my messages just in case. Make sure to wear your Yang merch!!!

If you would like to participate in the event after the Yanging, feel free to do so. Guidelines are on the Miami Bike Scene website:
https://www.themiamibikescene.com/p/miami-critical-mass-guidelines.html

We're *strongly* encouraging everyone to sign up at "peak hours" 2:00PM CT - 6:00PM CT in order to minimize the wait time between calls.
